Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Trajectory", "::", "usage"}], 
   "=", "\"\<Trajectory[\[Rho]ini\[Rule]operator, events] generates a \
trajectory function for the expectation value of operator, when the initial \
density operator \[Rho]ini is propagated under the specified events.  \
Trajectory[\[Rho]ini\[Rule]{op1,op2..}, events] generates a set of trajectory \
functions for several different operators. \nThe option NormalizationFactor \
is used to control the vertical scale of the trajectories. If \
NormalizationFactor\[Rule]number, the trajectories are divided by number. If \
NormalizationFactor\[Rule]operator, the trajectories are divided by the \
normalized LiouvilleBracket of \[Rho]ini and the reference operator. This \
syntax is useful when handling thermal equilibrium density operators. \
NormalizationFactor\[Rule]False disables the normalization. The option \
EnsembleAverage may be used to average the trajectories over a set of values \
for any parameter. In this case, the option InterpolationPoints specifies the \
number of points used for interpolation when combining the ensemble \
trajectories.\nThe output of Trajectory is one or more TrajectoryFunction \
objects.\n\>\""}], ";"}]], "Input",
 PageWidth:>WindowWidth,
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.452685645562502*^9, 3.45268596259144*^9}, {
