Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"MaximizeTransformationAmplitude", "::", "usage"}], 
   "=", "\"\<MaximizeTransformationAmplitude[\[Rho]ini\[Rule]obs,events,{{p1,\
p1ini},{p2,p2ini}..}, opts] numerically optimizes a TransformationAmplitude \
quantity with respect to parameters {p1,p2..}, starting from initial \
parameter values {p1ini,p2ini..}. \nThe option rules opts may include \
BackgroundGenerator and any of the other usual option specifications for \
TransformationAmplitude. The values specified in opts may depend on the \
parameters {p1,p2..}.\\nThe option rules opts may include the directive \
ConstrainPositive\[Rule]True which constrains all parameters {p1,p2..} to \
positive values. The syntax ConstrainPositive\[Rule]{p1,p2..} may be used to \
constrain only a subset of parameters to positive values. This is frequently \
required for pulse sequence delays, etc., which cannot take negative values. \
\nMore general constraints may be implemented by using \
MaximizeTransformationAmplitude[\[Rho]ini\[Rule]obs,events,{{p1,p1ini,{p1min,\
p1max}}..}, opts] subjects the parameter p1 to the constraint p1min\
\[NonBreakingSpace]\[LessEqual]\[NonBreakingSpace]p1\[NonBreakingSpace]\
\[LessEqual]\[NonBreakingSpace]p1max. If the maximum value p1max is omitted, \
there is no upper constraint. Any of the parameters {p1,p2..} may be \
constrained in this way.  \nConstrained optimization is often computationally \
more intensive than unconstrained optimization.\n\
MaximizeTransformationAmplitude deploys the Mathematica routine FindMinimum \
to find a local minimum of the negative transformation amplitude, starting \
from a specified point. The rules specified in opts may include \
specifications for FindMinimum, including a value for the Method option (see \
the documentation for FindMinimum).\\nThe output of \
MaximizeTransformationAmplitude has the form {maxval,rules} where maxval is \
the optimized value of the TransformationAmplitude and rules specify the \
values of the optimized parameters. \>\""}], ";"}]], "Input",
 PageWidth:>WindowWidth,
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.452685645562502*^9, 3.45268596259144*^9}, {
